The paper deals with graph search protocols and algorithms on cocomparability graphs, which are a type of directed acyclic graph (DAG). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves the study of posets and their complements, which falls under cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The use of LexDFS as a preprocessing step suggests that the paper may also be relevant to cs.CG (Computational Geometry) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Finally, the paper deals with graph theory and optimization problems, which could be relevant to cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
